    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "It was me who reported this on the mailing list.\n\nThe problem: When `KernelManager.kernel_cmd` is set in the configuration (let's say in `ipython_config.py` to be concrete), the command-line option `--debug` no longer has an effect on the kernel process, even if `kernel_cmd` is set to exactly the same value that it defaults to.\n\nFollowing the suggestion by @Carreau, I set `IPKernelApp.log_level='DEBUG'` in the configuration, which works fine. So the bug seems to be in passing on the `--debug` flag to `IPKernel`.\n"
  },
