    "updated_at": "2014-01-27T19:39:35Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The notebook forwards command-line args to the kernel by default. Setting kernel_cmd overrides this behavior, and assumes that you are setting the _entire_ kernel_cmd. This is because when you set kernel_cmd, IPython doesn't know whether that's the IPython kernel, IHaskell, or something else, and it can't assume that all kernels support all the command-line flags that IPython does (this includes `--debug`).\n\nThe message logging is done by the Kernel, triggered by adding `--debug` to `kernel_cmd`, so you will have to reimplement it in IHaskell anyway.\n\nI'm not sure there is any bug here.\n"
  },
