    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Ah! I did not realize that `--debug` was to the _kernel_ not to the _server_. What I thought it did was log all _received_ messages _from_ the kernel - is there a way to do that?\n\nAlso, how can we make it so that arguments are passed to the kernel, slash is that possible? I tried to find a way to do that and if you use `kernel_cmd` it looks like that's impossible (if I remember correctly what either @minrk or @Carreau  said...) It seems very strange to have a default behaviour which is actually _impossible_ to replicate if you use your own kernel.\n\nBut it looks like this isn't a bug, so it should probably be closed, although there may be some feature requests here...\n"
  },
